  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2004-10-07",
    "date": "2004-11-18T16:08:36Z",
    "text": "Up-Skilling Tax Credit Act of 2004 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a general business tax credit for up to 20 percent of the cost of technical training for employees performing services in a trade or business of the taxpayer. Limits the amount of the credit to $1,000 for each employee, reduced by credit amounts for all prior taxable years. Terminates the credit after 2008."
  },
